 closure2.class$ during deserialization for better coverage.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Examining synthetic methods**\\n\\nI’m looking into the synthetic helper method for class literals, which is a fallback for pre-Java 5. It’s possible that it’s not referenced anywhere. I wonder if running `javap -c -p FormAuthFilter` would reveal any references to closure2.class$, but I don't think it does. \\n\\nHmm, maybe I should search the bytecode for references directly instead to see if I can find any clues about its usage or behavior. That might lead to better insight!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_w3zaAZ31ZWYq3nHbv3i9RZTe|fc_0796b18e1f3a5d1d016a282a0f2d888196a82ba7d84aca2c75", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "for c in FormAuthFilter FormAuthFilter\\$_filter_closure2; do echo $c; javap -classpath /home/vjovanov/.gradle/caches/modules-2/files-2.1/io.rest-assured/rest-assured/5.5.0/1bc7b4c046c2e00a37bf78f2d9d7b41a43fdd5d1/rest-assured-5.5.0.jar -c -p io.restassured.internal.filter.$c | grep -n \"class\\$\\|forName\"; done"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 9633, "output": 917, "cacheRead": 44544, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 55094, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1781017075682, "responseId": "resp_0796b18e1f3a5d1d016a2829f4ce6c8196a66765b864f7bde7"}}
